        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 6 at 10:54PM MDT until June 6 at 11:30PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 1054 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Clovis,
moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Emergency management reported half dollar size hail in
Clovis.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect
wind damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Clovis, Texico, Ranchvale, Cannon Air Force Base, Portair and
Pleasant Hill.

This includes Highway 60 between Mile Markers 380 and 397.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. This storm is capable of producing damaging winds and has
produced large hail.</instruction>
